@node "intro" "Introduction - We have come full circle!"

Introduction:

 This  manual  is meant to help you use TrapConfig.  It is also meant to be
more  than  a  BIT entertaining.  You see, we like what we do, playin' with
them  there  'Miga  compooters.   Can't get enough of them.  Kinda like the
puppies  we  never  had  as children, you know?  I mean I wanted one really
bad,  I  begged,  I  pleaded,  but all my parents did was give me a Siamese
Fighting  Fish, and named it "Rover".  It died the first time I took it for
a  walk, on a leash.  Sniff.  But Rover multitasked as well as a Macintosh.
That's why I got an Amiga.

 Sorry.   I  digress.  But these being "Gonzo Docs" your humble author will
be  doing  that a lot.  So what.  This isn't Rocket Science.  It's Computer
Science.  Big diff.

So  We  hope these docs will be a help.  Some of them have been culled from
the  "Official"  TrapDoor docs, for reference, and have little "addendums",
with  tricks,  tips,  and  clarifications, sprung from years of beating our
heads  against the TrapDoor.  Keep in mind, this program is so easy to use,
to  generate  a TrapDoor.cfg file, you can train an ape to do it.  In fact,
one of our beta testers is a Cerebus Monkey, with a 4000/030.

Smart bastard. Wears diapers, but a smart bastard.

New TrapDoor/TrapConfig users: BOY! are you getting off easy!

***************************************************************************

Our story, thus far:

   Mendicant goes to Mount Olympus and meets the Pastry Eatin' Austrians

  We hearkin back, gentle readers, to that town in Baja Oklahoma Central, a
town  known  for  it's  centers  of  higher learning; a town known for it's
spirited  nightlife  and  deep understanding of combat pharmacology; a town
known  for  it's  inordinate  population  of the human sub-species known as
"Slackers";  a  town known for a club called "The BackRoom", and the tenure
of one "Borneo Bob" McNeely therein; a town known for incredible numbers of
mind-numbingly  beautiful and intelligent women.  Most of all, this town is
known  for  it's  stupifying  population  of  the  human sub-genus "Weenyus
Computerum".   In  a town like this, there is one name that is, to all that
know,  like  that  of  the rough beast that slouches towards Jerusalem.  In
this  town  that  waggles  it's genatalia in the general direction of Steve
Jackson,  Tom  Jennings,  and  Bill  Gates,  just  because  it's  good form
(Besides,  real men use UNIX), there is one amongst them that can clear the
street.  Last time anyone even ATTEMPTED a computer show here, the hall was
cleared of customers and vendors in 5 minutes, just on the basis of a rumor
of  this  person's  imminent  arrival.  This is the person whom it has been
rumored  that  was  the  single-handed  cause of Microsoft's dropping Amiga
development.   This  in spite of the fact that Bill Gates has been heard to
say,  more  than  once, "Thank GOD for the Amiga", just because this person
owns  one.   His ownership of what is, at least nominally, an Amiga is said
to  have figured highly in Dave Haynie's departure from Commodore, and some
say, his training in classical Japanese warrior arts, since Dave is rumored
to  feel that you can't be too ready should you be confronted by this Amiga
Anathema.   Randall  Jessup  has  considered  studying Ninjutsu, just so he
could  infiltrate  Mehdi  Ali's house, to leave this person behind, knowing
the deadly consequences.

  By  now,  gentle  readers, you probably know where this is leading.  Yes,
ugly  as it is, it has come time to check up on Him.  He that is the pimple
made  flesh.  The man so grossly constipated, he couldn't get an enema from
a  fire  hose.   The  man whose name is synonomous with "Cold-Packed Cheese
Food".

  Get  used  to it.  We just won't release any new software without a visit
from "He, that is the Reason id Systems will Never Port Doom to The Amiga".

  Ladies and Gentlemen, I give you the the man that caused Motorola to hire
hitmen,  the  man  that  SINGLEHANDEDLY has stalled the aquisition of Amiga
technology  by interested third parties, due to widespread, bowel-loosening
fear:

  <ruffles and flourishes> MENDICANT-BOB ODOM!!!!  <ta da>

  As  we  look  in  on  our  hero,  we  notice  significent  changes to his
neighborhood,  since  we  last  visited.   Every  other house, for a 5 mile
radius  of  our  hero's double-wide, has installed the latest in razor wire
technology.   Some  of  the  more  concerned  home owners have installed an
element  of  design  known as "Fortifications and gun slits".  One affluent
and forward thinking homeowner has installed General Electric 20mm electric
gatling guns with laser target aquisition, and intersecting fields of fire.
Needless  to  say,  keeping  up with the joneses is the order of the day in
this less than bucolic neighborhood.

  What could be the cause of this arms race?

  Well,  our  hero  thinks  he  knows.  Of late, he has started to think IT
MIGHT  BE  HIM!   That perhaps people percieve him as different.  That they
don't like him?  Why could that be(Our Hero rarely looks into the mirror)?

  This  situation  has  taken  a sad and ugly turn, of late.  Mendicant has
developed  a  drinking  problem.   He  has  become a wretched, swinish mess
(Which,  in  comparison to his usual state, is nauseating in extremis).  He
sleeps  little  .  He usually justs gazes into his pathetic, long suffering
1084s  monitor,  gazing  half heartedly on his vast collection of Knightly,
studly  .GIF's and .JPEG's, wondering where it has gone wrong.  Needless to
say,  WHAT  he  is  drinking has contributed greatly to this present state.
Sweet  Bleedin'Jesus on a Garage Creeper, has he started drinking the heavy
stuff!  MIXED DRINKS, AND WHAT MIXED DRINKS!

  Big  Red,  Jolt, and Snapple Iced Tea(Peach).  Right now, Young Mr.  Odom
would  probably  be  killed by a massive static discharge if he came near a
cold  water  pipe, so utterly tweeked and geeked is his nervous system.  He
has  not been able to keep down a decent and nutritious meal of 7-11 Deluxe
Nachos  for  days.  He is a human auto wreck, wracked by doubts of his true
standing  in  the  Amiga BBS community.  Where did he go wrong?  He got all
the  software  running!  He had all the Knightly, Studly Pictures!  He even
registered  Hack  and Slash!  He even got CNET, because he believed it when
this guy named Rod, whom he met in the AMY_TECH echo told him it would make
him too cool for school, too tough for TV.  Besides, that nasty Trew fellow
was picking on poor Bill, so he couldn't POSSIBLY run DLG, and Rod told him
that  Tom  Dietz had stolen so much of CNET's code that poor Ken was on the
verge  of  a  massive  nervous breakdown.  Mendy felt so bad he just had to
send in the $974.36 registration fee that he was told was needed.

  While sitting around feeling existentially sorry for himself, there was a
knocking on the bedroom door.  Quickly disengaging himself from the task at
hand, and zipping up his pants, he bleated "CuuuuuuuMIN?!!".

  The door crashed inwards; "Geekmeister!  Is that a pimple in your pocket,
or are you glad to see me?".

  It was his sister Mindy, whom he hadn't seen since she was a character in
a  game  the  Arexx  god  keep  promising to release, PANDIMONIUM.  She was
wearing,  yet  again, that suit of many holes, the suit he had seen worn by
the  Titian-haired  goddess  whom  did consort with his true protector, the
AREXX GOD!

  It  should  now  be noted that the similarities between Mendy, and Mindy,
are  few.  I mean, let's get it clear; someone pissed in Mendy's gene pool.
There  is  little  chance that Mendy will ever sire progeny.  The man would
have to be a ninja to sneak up on a glass of water, to get a drink.  Not so
Mindy.

  Mindy  is  living proof that nature can be cruel, to siblings.  She looks
like a one woman "Snap-On Tools" calendar.  Plans are afoot to dedicate one
full  issue  of  "Penthouse  Letters"  to her, but the volume of mail is so
stupendous,  they  are  considering  a 7 volume set, bound in unborn gerbil
skin.   She  is  6 feet tall, in her stocking feet, but she usually wears 6
inch  f***  me  pumps.  She has waist length blond hair, in a leonine mane.
She is incredibly blessed in the mamalian protruberance department, and her
supportive  connective  tissue  is  in  such  good  working  order that she
normally  eschews  undergarments,  agressively.   She,  in the past, taught
Sharon Stone how to make new friends by crossing her legs.  She has a MENSA
gold  card.  She has a simple Philosophy:  "My sexuality is my sandbox, and
I  WILL play in it, anytime I damn well please!".  She makes alleycats look
like  Pat Robertson.  She thinks Erik Petersen is cute, and plans to really
make  him  look  like a debauched college professor, just as soon as Health
Canada  allows her entry above the 54th Parrelel.  She normally wears Black
leather, with studs on the Inside.  The number of men that wish to bear her
children numbers in the thousands.

  She   asks,   in   a   manner   that   is,   for   her,  delicate:   "So,
Pizza-countainence, what has your panties in a wad?"

  "Well  Mindy,  first,  I  must ask you, what brings you back to this fair
city?  Last I knew, you were teaching your specialties to unfortunate young
women in Bangkok."

  "I  tired of the heat, and humidity, so I decided to return here for real
heat and humidity.  I have a new job!"

  "What are you doing now?"

  "I'm  working  in  the  defense  industries,  offering  my body up in the
defense of our country." (Authors Note:  It's a big country, the U.S.A.)

  "Neat!  What is it you do?"

  "Well,  Mendy,  this  job is VERY sensitive to our national interests.  I
must  insist  that you never tell anyone, for it could directly imperil our
national defense!"

  "I  assure  you,  dear sister, that I would NEVER say anything that would
impact  adversely  on  our  national  defense.  After all, I listen to Rush
Limbaugh!"

  "That  CERTAINLY  speaks VOLUMES about you, as an American!" Mindy's eyes
rolled back in her head.

She continued:

  "Well,  when  they  launch  Jet  Aircraft  from  Bergstrom, I start their
engines!"

  "Really?  With Batteries, and such?"

  "No.  I am what you would call "Emergency Standby Power".

  "HUH?"

  "Well,  If  the  B-52's  won't start, I use my superior lung power to get
them online"

  "WHA?"

  "Look, fecal-cranial interface, I SUCK START B-52's!"

  Our  hero ponders this revelation for a moment, and then decides this all
makes  very good sense.  After all, didn't all the kids in the neighborhood
say she had really great lungs?

  She  asks:  "So, now you spill.  Why you hitting the hard stuff?  Jeezus,
you look so bad you would gag a maggot, which is nothing really new, all in
all."

  "Well,  Mindy, I have begun to doubt myself, and my position in the Amiga
Sysop  community.   I  thought  I  had made all the right moves, especially
after I became a CNET sysop.  Bill Beogelein won't even talk to me!"

  "WHEW!   Jeez,  he  talks  to  himself  so much, you'd think he'd welcome
another viewpoint.  Even so, I'd bet he'd look cute all done up in a frilly
french  maid's  uniform!   What's  his  nodenumber?   What's  that command?
GETNODE?  Do you remember his node number?"

  "MINDEEEE!   Can't  you  put your carnal needs aside!  I am swimming in a
sea of existential uncertainty!  Besides, Bill is married, I think..."

  "What about that clever Rick Lembree?  Is he available?  He's SOOO witty,
it makes me moist!  GETNODE, right?"

  Our  hero,  having reached his emotional limit, bows his head and quietly
begins to sob.

  His sister speaks:

  "AWWW!  Poor Maroon, you are SOOO tense.  Let me massage you neck.  Don't
get  any  ideas,  though.   Even  though  I  am  Editor Emeritis for FAMILY
AFFAIRS,  you  and  I  can  never consummate our relationship, even with me
ingesting  mega-doses  of  anti-nauseants, and beta blockers.  So don't get
any ideas!"

  Our hero was confused by this, since he rarely had an idea, and had given
up on the concept.  All he wanted was respite from this veil of tears.

  Mindy's  talented  hands  started  their  work.   Hands  that had stopped
division-level  military engagements in Serbo-Croatia kneeded his rock-hard
neck  muscles.   His  sleep-deprived  mind  started  to  drift  towards the
embracing  arms  of  Hypnos  and Morpheus,which scared Our Hero, since they
were  dressed  in Jockstraps, and black leather hoods, with a 55 gallon Kit
Drum  of  Crisco  at  their  feet.   His  head lolled forward and back.  He
drooled.   His  sister thought; "Good, he's drooling.  He must be returning
to normal."

  Our  Hero  opens  his eyes, finally, and all he sees is green.  His first
thought  is "What is this?  Have I finally gone blind?  I was only going to
do  it  until I needed glasses." He tries to raise himself up and discovers
that  both  his  arms have gone to sleep.  He rolls over and discovers that
yes,  he  has been drooling in his sleep, and the back of his head is lying
in it.  He sees blue sky above him.  Impossibly blue.  Severe clear.  Warm,
but not hot.  Comfortably dry.  A zephyr.  A ZEPHYR?!!!!?!!?!!?!!?!!?

  He  sits  up, his two still useless arms dangling like a couple of tingly
wet  dishcloths at his side.  Looking around, he feels his surroundings are
strangely  familiar.   There  is  a river, a green meadow, and a Pub called
"The  King's  Head",  with Directors on tap.  Could this be Shepperton, yet
again?   Our  Hero  silently hopes that this is Sunday, so he can go to the
Anchor, for Sunday Lunch.

  Off  in  the distance, he senses a commotion.  NAH!  It couldn't be!  Not
again?

  Over  the green hillock comes two VERY large fellows, spitting images for
the  two tax collectors from HACK&SLASH, bearing a struggling form bound in
a burlap bag.  One speaks:

  "OI!  Guv, would you be one Mendicant-Bob Odom?  The<gag> Amiga Wally?"

  "My name is Mendicant, yes.  Not Wally."

  "<gordon  bennett, what a prat!> Well, me old son, we have a delivery for
you,  from one Mr.  Irving Gould, late of Commodore Business Machines, Ltd.
He considers you unfinished business best disposed of quickly."

  "What  is  the  nature of this delivery" < a muffled scream is heard from
inside  the  bag.  One of the fellows lays a large, meaty paw into the bag,
with gusto.  A muffled grunt, and fart, is heard.>

  "Well  sir,  it  is  what we understand to normally be the answer to your
prayers."

  Finally,the  bag  wrenches itself from the grasp of the two oafs who bear
an  uncanny  resemblence  to  a Derek and Clive sketch, minus the lobsters.
The bag bursts open:

  SCHMUCK!   DILLWEED!   PISSANT!   DOOFUS!   YOU  ARE THE BANE OF MY LIFE!
DEATH, WHERE IS THY STING!  WILL I EVER BE FREE OF YOU!

  Our  hero, while his heart skips a beat, genuflects:  "OH!  AREXX GOD!  I
KNEW you wouldn't fail me in my hour of need!"

  "Cut  the  crap,  buttwipe.  Every time I gotta get the docs out,I end up
feeling  soiled!   Why  do  I feel soiled?  Because I have to deal with the
likes of you!"

  Our  Hero  feels  true love.  But it is the pure love that can only exist
between two men, one of whom is an Arexx God.  Warmth infuses him.

  "Don't  look  at me like that, closet case.  Besides, there is a world of
hurt  on  the  way.  Death doesn't ride a pale horse, today.  Death rides a
Harley."

  Over  the  rise  comes, in midair, a Fatbob, ridden by her.  The focus of
every  misunderstood  urge  Our  Hero  has  ever  felt.   The Titian-haired
goddess.  The consort of the Arexx God.  Wearing Leather.  With Lace.

  "AHHHHHHH!   CRETIN!   I  hold im my hand one end of MILLIONS of miles of
16-2  electrical  cord.   As  I  promised,  the other end is attached to my
electric  blanket  controller.  At the other end sits the God-mother, J.C.,
awaiting  my psychic command to turn your procreative nodules into raisins!
So  stop  your  grinnin'  and  drop  your linen!  I have had enough of your
stuff!   We can set our watch by you!  Someone loads CED in New Jersey, and
we gotta hunt for our passports!"

  Our  hero  shuddered.   He  then detected ANOTHER clamor in the distance.
Over  the  ridge came MINDY!  Riding a white charger(Who ran the whole time
with  a  woody,  and  soulful  eyes,  gazing  upon  her,  while  smoking  a
cigarette).

  Our Hero Speaks:

  "Mindee!  What are you doing in my food-based hallucination?"

  "Well,  I  wasn't  going to miss this chance to make new friends, even if
they  have  the bad taste to be your friend, too.  By the way, I can make a
little  magic, too.  Look at what your wearing.  Hey, your Arexx God friend
looks like fun.  Can I borrow him?  I'll give you back the parts you need."

 The goddess, on the Harley, mumbled.  "Bitch.  Slut.  I like her.."

  Our Hero looked down.  He was wearing the suit of many holes!  OH MY!  He
had arrived!

  The  goddess asks:  "Uhhh, is that a nasty pimple you have there, in your
nether regions?  Oh, NO!  Never mind..."

  Our  hero  blushes,  but  do  to  the terminally unfortunate state of his
complexion,  this goes unnoticed by all in attendance.  A thought struggles
across  our  hero's  cerebral cortex, kind of like a slug crawling across a
cold puddle of molasses:  "Nice threads, but where do I put my penholder?"

  The  Arexx  God,  in a state of terminal pique, speaks:  "This is it, you
sick  little monkey!  Time to meet your fate.  But your fate will not be at
MY hands!  We are going to take a little trip, so hang onto your goolies."

  Mindy  asks:  "Do I have time to do my hair, and nails?  Can we go to the
Reeperbahn?   I  hear  that  I  could  find a plethora of job opportunities
there!"

  The  Arexx  God  holds  up  a  sceptre, marked with celtic runes that are
rumored  to  spell  "Dineen-Edwards".   He  screams  the magic incantation.
"'ADDRESS COMMAND (C:HAUL_ASS)'" The is a large flash of light, and a sound
like  the  whirring of a cosmic hard drive, in bad need of an optimization.
Smoke,  flames,  and  SLAYER  music fills there senses.  The last thing Our
Hero hears before he slips into insensation is Mindy:  "Hey, Red, you wanna
hear  about  the  time  I  got busy with Ozzy's road crew, in the back of a
Silver  Eagle  Tour  Bus, in Lincoln, Nebraska?  They canceled the tour the
next day!"

  An enveloping darkkness falls across the red, rheumy eyes of our hero.


CHAPTER II.- Our hero sits on a profiterole, and learns True Love.

  When  our  hero  awakes, yet again (Unconciousness is his friend...), his
eyes  fall  upon  a  Tootsie-Roll.   At least it looks tantilizingly like a
Tootsie-Roll.  Feeling in need of sustenance, he extends a hand towards the
tasty  looking  morsel.   The  voice  of  the Arexx god rings out:  "Uhhhh,
smegma-brain,  look where your laying.  Ask yourself; If I were laying in a
gutter,  as  you  are,  and I saw what looks to be a Tootsie Roll, should I
feel  secure in the the thought of eating it?  Believe me, dimbulb, if that
IS  a  Tootsie  Roll,  it  is  one  left  over from the final scene of PINK
FLAMINGOES."

  "Uhhh...(Our hero does his best Butthead), does that mean I shouldn't eat
it?"

  "No, schmuck.  Trust me.  Don't eat it.  It's used dog food."

  "What  am  I  to do, Arexx God?  I haven't eaten anything with stupifying
amounts  of  sugar  in  it  in  at  LEAST an hour!  This adventure stuff is
starting to upset my delicate chemical imbalance!"

  "Well, Cousin Gastric, You are in luck!  We have transported, through the
magic  of  Arexx, and the Dinneen-Edwards Compiler, to VIENNA!  Why Vienna?
Two  reasons:  One, this is the home of fine pastry.  Everybody knows that!
I  didn't  want you to die of malnutrition.  Two, we have come here for you
to  be  judged  by the massed numbers of your fellow Amiga Sysops, who have
gathered  here  to be witness to that rarest of events; the introduction of
the  latest  version  of  the One True Trapdoor.  No one is exactly sure of
when  this  paradigm  shift  in  man's telecommunacatory evolution has last
taken place.  Various gods and demigods of the Amiga Sysop pantheon will be
in  attendence.   You  will have your one chance to see if you have what it
takes  to  be  one  of  their  elite  number.   Fail  here, and you will be
condemned to an eternity of trying to get a BBS to run on a Mac."

  A  thought  crossed  our hero's mind (Authors note:  Right now, we should
examine  the  process of a thought crossing the sere and eldritch landscape
that  is  the mind of Mendicant-Bob Odom (Rhymes with Modem...).  This will
best  illustrate;  Imagine  a  well  salted  slug  crawling,  on a sub-zero
winter's  day,  across  a six foot puddle of near-frozen molasses.  You get
the  picture,  I'm sure.  It has been said that if you put our hero's brain
on  the  edge  of a razor blade, it would look like a well-oiled BB rolling
down a 4 lane highway).  The thought, not recognizing the surroundings, and
not  liking  them,  either, does what any self-respecting thought would do.
It flees.

  Our  Hero looks up, from the Viennese gutter, to the building in front of
him.   He  adjusts  his glasses.(Well, not really GLASSES!  They really are
contact  lenses  with a nosepiece, and ear pieces.).  His eyes, after there
usual requisite 30 second delay, focus on the sign:

                          "The AMIGA_SYSOP CAFE"
                       "Propriator: Frank Perricone"
                          "Under NEW Ownership!"

  Our  Hero  notices workmen disassembling scaffolding, in the front of the
cafe.   One  is taking away a sign that says PRES-something.  He feels that
he  has  seen this cafe before.  Hmmm, where has he seen it?  It looks sooo
familiar!   AHA!   It looks like that movie Mindy had brought home, to show
him!   The one she said would help him learn to possibly salvage his social
life,  the  one with Al Pacino, in the police hat.  What was that called...
Cruising!  That was it.  He didn't get it.

  "Well, Mallomar-breath, Let's go inside, your public awaits.  By the way,
the women will be along, directly.  Your sister has taken my consort to her
favorite  toystore, here in Vienna.  Something called "The Pleasure Chest".
Mindy promised me that Christmas, this year, will be memorable."

  As  the  approach  the  door,  they  notice  that a foundry-like noise is
emanating from the establishment.

  "Hmm, sounds like here there be Amiga Sysops!" The Arexx God Intones.

  As  the  door opens outwards, Our Hero gazes upon a scene unlike anything
he  has  ever seen.  A fight, like that of Mel Brook's History of The World
Part  II,  Casino  Royale, and comp.sys.amiga.advocacy, COMBINED, is taking
place  in the cafe.  Chairs, Tables, pastries, 3.5" floppy disks, and other
detritus  is flying higgledy-piggledy.  Bodies are being tossed to and fro.
The vilest of epithets are being hurled.

  "Why  are  they  fighting,  O  He  that Understands the Cosmic Meaning of
Iteration?!"

  "This?   A  FIGHT?   Feh!  This is just Amiga Sysops enjoying their usual
spirited  dialectic!   If  this was a real fight, there would be those from
The  Dark  Legions  of  The  Blue  Poughkeepsieans, and possibly their Evil
Prince  of  Discord,  He who is called Gates.  Then you would see fighting.
Those  from  the  Tribe  of  Cupertino  never  cross  our  path.   They are
sequestered in their hermitages, trying to get their System of The Seven to
work.   Seems  they  have  this legend of a hidden command line, the search
after  which  keeps  them  occupied.   All  in  all,  an  effite lot, thoes
Cupertinians!.   Why,  they  don't even know how to cook fish!  Hence, they
are condemned to a life of eating their fish raw!  They even profess liking
it that way!"

  Our hero's mind reeled at all he was being forced to absorb.  He was also
forced to supress a gag:  "Cold, raw fish?" He couldn't imagine it.  He was
thankful,  yet  again,  for  the  existance of 7-11, and Deluxe Nachos with
cheese and extra denatured jalapenos.

  All of a sudden a whistle pierces the air:  "Hey, can you guys stop for a
moment?!"  It was The Titian-Haired Goddess.  She was back from here little
shopping  trip, with Mindy in tow:  "Do you think we girls can dissuade you
fellows  from your testosterone-fueled dialog, for a while, and maybe, just
maybe, we can get this new Trapdoor released, and get Numb-Nuts other sysop
testicle  to  drop,  in  a manner of speaking?" Getting this rabble to stop
their  knuckled  ministrations was NOT too hard, at all.  There before them
stood two, fetching visions, dressed in something that would cause the need
for  last-minute  adjustments in a dead man's coffin.  The cafe was silent,
except for the sound of drool hitting the floor, especially from the corner
of  the  room  that  held  the  largest  number  of those from the Tribe of
Ami-Express.   They were easily spotted by the eyepatches, Jaunty seafaring
garb,  parrots on their shoulders, and Jolly Roger flying over their table.
Software authors avoided them, aciduously.

  Mindy,  ever  the  showoff,  wass wearing a variation on The Suit of Many
Holes,  except  that  this  was  ONE  BIG  HOLE!   On  the  other hand, The
Titian-Haired  Goddess  was  not dressed differently.  "Woojums", The Arexx
God asked, "Didn't you buy any clothes for yourself?"

  "No,  I didn't!  You think I was going to traipse around in front of this
lot  in  something  revealing,  you are sadly mistaken!.  I don't flaunt in
front of sociopaths!"

  "But what's in the bags and boxes?  What's in the really big one?"

  "I  went to The Pleasure Ches, and I bought TOYS!  For Christmas!  As for
the  really  big  one, I will only say this:  It's Slippery, and there is a
lot of it!  Now, will you get this ceremony over with!  I want to get home,
away  from Super Weeny, and all of his cellmates from the asylum.  And open
the big one, teehee."

  One member of the audience stood up:  "I take umbrage with any comparison
with  Pus Boy!  I am Mr.  BBS, and as such cannot be considered as an equal
to  such  a pitiable mess." On that note, a pile formed on top of Mr.  BBS,
not because he said anything too objectionable, just because it seemed like
the  thing  to  do.   While the pile was formed, others voted on whether to
throw Mr.  BBS out, for the mere fact he drew breath, or just to squash him
like a bug.  Squashing was popular amongst a group of canadians.

  Suddenly,  a great fanfare was heard!  Trumpets, flugelhorns, english and
french horns!  Steve Vai on lead!  Tympani!  The lights dimmed.  Varilights
swept  the room.  One wall fell away, to reveal a splendid stage, with what
seemed  to  be  the  set from the 1984 Quiet Riot tour on it.  Finally, the
fanfare reached a crescendo and spotlights fell on stage right.  Out walked
three  unremarkable  men, dressed in, well, just CLOTHES!  One had some Doc
Martens  on,  but  BIG  DEAL!   THESE  were The Mystic Knights of Trapland!
SHEESH!  What a ripoff!

  The first one to the podium speaks:  "Hi.  I'm Max, this is Rene, This is
Martin.   Here's Trapdoor 1.84.  Hope you enjoy it.  We have to go now.  We
must take our 54th vacation this year.  You all know just how stressful bug
stomping  can really be!" With that they start to walk off.  At that point,
something snaps in Our Hero:  "Wait!  What about my Ceremony, initiating me
into the full Amiga Sysopdom?  I've come so far, and tried so hard!  Will I
be condemned again?"

  Max  turns around:  "Oh, the Amiga Potato Head!  Sorry, but the stress of
this  release party has my brain in SUCH a tizzy!  I almost forgot you, and
while  you are eminantly forgettable, in a traumatic amnesia sort of way, I
suppose  you  do  deserve a fair shake.  For the life of me, I really don't
know  WHAT the big deal is!  I deal with Amiga Sysops every day, and I will
tell you this; you are no more a loser than any of them.  No less either."

  With  that,  Max  gave  a  cue, and a LARGE mirrored panel started a slow
descent to the floor.  As he turned and left, Max said:  "See for yourself.
Just  don't  call  me  for  at least another two years.  Period.  God!  The
stress!"

  The  mirror  stopped.  Mendicant looked into it, waiting the usual twenty
or  so  minutes  it  took for his eyes to go through their lengthy focusing
ritual.  Once he could see, his heart nearly exploded with Joy!  He was NOT
unique  in  the universe!  Everywhere he looked, there was someone else who
seemed  to  be just like him!  Guys like Rick, Rich, Brian, Alan, Jonathan,
Frank,  Jim...Gee,  they were just like him!  He was like them!  Koo Koo Ka
Shoo!   They  all  had  their "Pimples" hanging out in public!  Their asses
too!  Some even had their asses on their shoulders, something he had always
been afraid to try!

  The  Arexx  God whispered to him:  "See?  Now, you've snatched the pebble
from my hand, buttwipe !"

  *BLAM*

  Our  hero  awoke  in his room, just after the men from FEMA declared it a
toxic  disaster  area.   Something  was  different, though.  Instead of his
Amiga 250, there was a shiny new 4000/040!  On it was a note:

  "So,  now  you  know.  You're just like all the others; weird, obsessive,
socially  maladjusted,  and malnourished to the point of psychosis.  Aren't
you  happy  to know that you keep such fine company?  BTW:  Don't EVER call
me again!"

  Our  hero  sat  down,  sighed  a happy sigh, and started rummaging in his
drawers.   He  pulled  out a screwdriver, a hammer, a ten penny nail, and a
200  mhz  MIPS  processor he just happend to have won in a marble game.  He
had this new design for a bridgeboard, you see...

  His  last thought, before applying himself to the task at hand was:  "Fat
chance, Rog, fat chance..."

@endnode

@node "pepsi" "System Requirements"
Requirements for TrapConfig V2.2:

  Workbench 2.0+

  libs:
     asl.library V36+
     intuition.library V37+
     graphics.library V37+
     gadtools.library V37+

  TrapDoor 1.83 +

All  the  required libs should be included with Workbench 2.0+.  The reason
for the Workbench 2.0 is because alot of the gadgets are 2.0 specific.

This  is  the  final  unregistered  release.   If  you  are  interested  in
registering  this  lovely utility, please refer to the docs directory.  All
the   information   that   you   need   is   located   in   a  file  called
Register.TXT..Enjoy!!!

TrapConfig is © 1993,94 BitMap Productions.

@endnode

@node "authors" "About the Authors"
Just who are these guys?

***************************************************************************

 Roger  Clark  is  a  fine, upstanding lad, who used to risk life and limb,
every  day, to protect our American Way of Life, in the U.S.  Air Force, by
hunting down weird bugs in their computers.  Roger left the Air Force, when
he  discovered  that  the  whole MILSTAR system was, in fact, a WPL mailer.
The  pain  was  so  great,  he  had  to  resign,  since he knew the obvious
consequences.

 Roger  is  also  the author of fine Arexx cheesy comestibles for TrapDoor,
TransAmiga,  and Foozle.  He is something of an Arexx guru (But in the best
possible  taste.   His  stuff NEVER crashes.), and is the moderator of many
Fidonet  echos,  including AMY_TECH, IVS and the EXCELSIOR!  support echos.
Roger  firmly  believes that SxSW is a formula we can all live by, and grow
with.   He  also  feels that Paintballs are a potent force for Peace in Our
Time.  Roger believes he can conquer World Hunger, with ARexx.

***************************************************************************

 Chaitanya "Chico" Marvici was also a bonded servent of the U.S.  Air Force
(Bergstrom  AFB.  Low Level Recon.  Wild Weasels.  30 year old F-4's.  Real
men.) He is the "C" grunt of the team.  He now makes a living playing games
16 hours a day for Origin Systems (lucky bastard!)

 Chaitanya's  hobby  is searching through University of Texas libraries, to
find  why someone with an Italian last name, would have an Indo-Asian first
name,  and  a Mexican nickname.  So far his search has been fruitless.  But
he  just got InterNet access.  You can just bet that Chico has a "Backroom,
for a hell of a good time!" T-shirt.

***************************************************************************

 Skal  Loret  is a 40 year old, broken-down, old roadie.  With Pretensions.
He  is overweight, has too much hair, a beard, bad knees, an Amiga 500 with
a  "Rock  LOBSTER" board (Fred Schneider just loves that!), a massive phone
bill, no girlfriend (except Amiga), and a well-honed taste for the bizarre.
For  some  reason, unbeknownst to him, he has been given the job of writing
the  docs  for TrapConfig.  This could be Trapconfig's fatal flaw.  Roger's
mother thinks Skal is weird.  Skal sees no need to disuade the good woman.

***************************************************************************
@endnode

